I’m going to talk about a habit that has really helped me concentrate on my studies, which is keeping my phone out of sight while working.

I started doing this about two years ago when I was in my second year at university. At that time, I struggled a lot with staying focused, so I went online to look for solutions. I came across a video on YouTube suggesting that phones are one of the biggest sources of distraction and should be kept away while studying.

At first, I didn’t take the advice seriously and continued to keep my phone next to me. However, I soon realized that whenever I received a notification, I would immediately check it, which constantly interrupted my concentration. That’s when I decided to make a change and started leaving my phone in another room during study sessions.

In the beginning, it was quite challenging because I was so used to using my phone and felt uncomfortable without it. Sometimes, I even had the urge to leave my desk just to check it. However, after about three weeks, I gradually got used to it and it became a habit.

This simple change has had a significant impact on my productivity. Without the constant distractions, I can now focus for several hours at a time and get much more work done. My screen time has also decreased considerably. Overall, I feel much more productive and in control of my time than I did before.

I would definitely recommend this method to anyone who struggles with concentration, as it’s surprisingly effective.
